in real life-ish. But let's get started. So I'm going to assume that the goal of creating

41
00:02:23,921 --> 00:02:28,605
a system-driven game is to create something emergent and uniquely interesting. Something

42
00:02:28,605 --> 00:02:33,649
that's more than the sum of its parts. If all you really wanted was A and then B and then C,

43
00:02:33,649 --> 00:02:37,973
obviously you would author it yourself. But writers are often frustrated by systems-based

44
00:02:37,973 --> 00:02:41,716
writing because we want to write towards an experience, and instead it often feels like

45
00:02:41,716 --> 00:02:42,717
we're asked to create a system-driven game.

46
00:02:43,297 --> 00:02:48,620
create a pile of unrelated words, phrases, and scenes, and after a while of creating

47
00:02:48,620 --> 00:02:52,562
these word piles, it's easy to feel like our efforts are actually less than the sum of

48
00:02:52,562 --> 00:02:53,983
our parts.

49
00:02:53,983 --> 00:02:58,746
And it's especially easy to combine these and make it feel predictable or repetitive,

50
00:02:58,746 --> 00:03:03,709
which Kate Compton has coined the oatmeal problem in her blog post, So You Want to Make a Generator.

51
00:03:05,538 --> 00:03:10,984
I can generate 10,000 bowls of oatmeal, each oat in a different position and orientation.

52
00:03:10,984 --> 00:03:14,328
And mathematically speaking, they will be completely unique.

53
00:03:14,328 --> 00:03:16,310
But the user will just see a lot of oatmeal.

54
00:03:16,310 --> 00:03:22,958
So she points out that what we're really looking for is perceptual uniqueness, not true uniqueness,

55
00:03:22,958 --> 00:03:23,819
just perceptual.

56
00:03:24,459 --> 00:03:29,122
And throughout this talk, I'm going to refer to that as meaning, which is kind of a fluffy,

57
00:03:29,122 --> 00:03:32,523
hippie word, but if you're more math-oriented, it makes you feel better.

58
00:03:32,523 --> 00:03:37,206
Feel free to think of it as perceptual uniqueness, because that is kind of what I mean.

59
00:03:37,206 --> 00:03:39,707
I'm just a little bit lazy and colloquial, I guess.

60
00:03:40,768 --> 00:03:44,630
