00:26:56,355 --> 00:26:59,497
Look, there's a new character being generated right now.

544
00:26:59,497 --> 00:27:03,779
So you can try different co-authors as part of the iteration process and see how it adds

545
00:27:03,779 --> 00:27:05,640
unexpected flavor and texture to your world.

546
00:27:06,987 --> 00:27:09,929
And you'll go around this loop a few times,

547
00:27:09,929 --> 00:27:11,410
but you'll find better results

548
00:27:11,410 --> 00:27:13,471
the more that you are able to measure them,

549
00:27:13,471 --> 00:27:16,173
not just as a writer for what jumps out at you

550
00:27:16,173 --> 00:27:19,475
as well written and what seems poorly constructed,

551
00:27:19,475 --> 00:27:21,236
but also at a very basic level,

552
00:27:21,236 --> 00:27:23,638
what does common actually mean?

553
00:27:23,638 --> 00:27:26,820
What does too surprising mean in your system?

554
00:27:26,820 --> 00:27:28,441
